sentences: Clive Parker (born 1960) also known as Clive Parker-Sharp, is an English drummer, active in the punk, post-punk and new wave genres.
In 1992, Parker had a minor dance hit with UK soul singer, Kasie Sharp, co-writing as part of the pop dance production team One Horse Man, who were also released by Arcade Records in Europe.
In 1979, Parker joined Spizzenergi, after auditioning at a small rehearsal room in arches at Waterloo, London.
In 1980, as Athletico Spizz 80, Parker played on the album, Do a Runner, which spent five weeks on the UK Albums Chart, peaking at number 27.
In 1980, the group appeared at the Futurama festival, along with Gary Glitter and Joy Division.
In 1980, after signing with A&M Records, the band toured the United States with 999.
The Box. - an historical biographical novel was released by Strand Publishing in 2012.
A semi-autobiographical novel released October 2018 by Box Productions.

He is now also a writer & published author, and plays guitar and keyboards.
Spizzenergi was a late 1970s punk rock/new wave band that changed its name several times during its existence.
In 1980, as Athletico Spizz 80, Parker played on the album, Do a Runner, which spent five weeks on the UK Albums Chart, peaking at number 27.
The album was recorded and mixed at Berry Street studios in London over the spring bank holiday weekend, and featured Jim Solar, Mark Coalfield, and Dave Scott in the line up.
The band played a week of sold-out shows at London's Marquee Club, with a matinee for younger fans.
Big CountryParker toured with Big Country, playing at the Dunfermline Glen Pavilion (first ever BC gig), and dates with Alice Cooper Armed Forces tour.
The Athletico Spizz 80 album is now housed in the British Library, as a reference tool.
